<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B52FFB3FF91FD3DFAFDFCED06A1" author="Mori, E. &amp; Magoga, G. &amp; Panella, M. &amp; Montagna, M. &amp; Winsor, L. &amp; Justine, J. &amp; Lou &amp; Menchetti, M. &amp; Schifani, E. &amp; Melone, B. &amp; Mazza, G." box="[699,878,1389,1413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" pagination="205 - 216" refId="ref3172" refString="Mori, E., Magoga, G., Panella, M., Montagna, M., Winsor, L., Justine, J. Lou, Menchetti, M., Schifani, E., Melone, B. &amp; Mazza, G. (2022) Discovering the Pandora's box: the invasion of alien flatworms in Italy. Biological Invasions, 24, 205 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10530 - 021 - 02638 - w" type="journal article" year="2022">
Mori 
<emphasis id="B912EAB1FFB3FF91FD71FAFEFCAD06A1" box="[759,814,1389,1413]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
). Here it is reported for the first time for the 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F841FFB3FF91FAC9FAFDFF65068D" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
. The presence of this species in 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F841FFB3FF91FDD4FA01FD28068D" box="[594,683,1425,1449]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Madeira</collectingRegion>
was published in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B52FFB3FF91FCF1FA01FBD0068D" author="Justine, J. - L. &amp; Winsor, L. &amp; Gey, D. &amp; Gros, P. &amp; Thevenot, J." box="[887,1107,1425,1449]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" pagination="8385" refId="ref2825" refString="Justine, J. - L., Winsor, L., Gey, D., Gros, P. &amp; Thevenot, J. (2020) Obama chez moi! The invasion of metropolitan France by the land planarian Obama nungara (Platyhelminthes, Geoplanidae). PeerJ, 8, e 8385. https: // doi. org / 10.7717 / peerj. 8385" type="journal article" year="2020">
Justine 
<emphasis id="B912EAB1FFB3FF91FC4CFA02FB80068D" box="[970,1027,1425,1449]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
as a personal communication without data regarding locality or collection date. Thus, this record confirms the presence of the species in 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F841FFB3FF91FABBFA25FA1A06E9" box="[1341,1433,1461,1485]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Madeira</collectingRegion>
. Sequences from 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F841FFB3FF91FECDFA49FE2706D5" box="[331,420,1497,1521]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Madeira</collectingRegion>
and the 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F841FFB3FF91FD84FA49FD2006D5" box="[514,675,1497,1521]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
match to the ‘network 3’ of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B52FFB3FF91FC5CFA49FB6C06D5" author="Lago-Barcia, D. &amp; Fernandez-Alvarez, F. A. &amp; Brusa, F. &amp; Rojo, I. &amp; Damborenea, C. &amp; Negrete, L. &amp; Grande, C. &amp; Norena, C." box="[986,1263,1497,1521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" pagination="289 - 302" refId="ref2895" refString="Lago-Barcia, D., Fernandez-Alvarez, F. A., Brusa, F., Rojo, I., Damborenea, C., Negrete, L., Grande, C. &amp; Norena, C. (2019) Reconstructing routes of invasion of Obama nungara (Platyhelminthes: Tricladida) in the Iberian Peninsula. Biological Invasions, 21, 289 - 302. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10530 - 018 - 1834 - 9" type="journal article" year="2019">
Lago-Barcia 
<emphasis id="B912EAB1FFB3FF91FBE1FA4AFB1D06D5" box="[1127,1182,1497,1521]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
, which includes sequences from 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FEC0FA6DFE060531" box="[326,389,1533,1557]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FE16FA6DFE6E0531" box="[400,493,1533,1557]" name="Portugal" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Portugal</collectingCountry>
